## IMPLEMENTATION PHASES

### Phase 1: Phase-to-Objection Mapping (Week 1)

**Deliverables:**
- Map all 200 handlers to call phases (Opening, TOF, MOF, BOF, Thesis, Integration, Close)
- Create "Most Likely" lists for each phase (5-7 handlers per phase)
- Validate mappings with call transcripts

**Success Criteria:**
- Every handler tagged with at least one phase
- Predictive lists capture 80%+ of objections in that phase

### Phase 2: Predictive UI Build (Week 2)

**Deliverables:**
- Build "MOST LIKELY OBJECTIONS" section in sidebar
- Connect to phase detection system (via progress tracker or questions)
- Auto-update predictive handlers as phase changes

**Success Criteria:**
- Predictive section shows correct handlers for current phase
- Updates automatically when rep advances

### Phase 3: Category Enhancement (Week 3)

**Deliverables:**
- Organize all 200 handlers into 10 categories
- Add counters showing number of handlers per category
- Make sections collapsible with expand/collapse functionality

**Success Criteria:**
- All handlers accessible via category browse
- No duplicates across categories
- Collapsible UI reduces visual clutter

### Phase 4: Search & Polish (Week 4)

**Deliverables:**
- Build emergency search with keyword + phase + category filters
- Add copy-to-clipboard buttons for scripts
- Implement handler detail view with all components

**Success Criteria:**
- Search returns accurate results in <1 second
- All handlers have Quick Response + Full Script + Key Principle
- Copy buttons work reliably

